ATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
The mapping %m ran in the %s session in the %w workflow ran in %d.
When this process fails and sets the RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD = 101 value, IT must research to determine the root cause ASAP. Once the root cause is determined, the oncall must do one of two things with the Recons in error (RCNT_RECN_SUMM_QUE.RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD = 101 and RECN_SUMM_TYP_CD > 1).
(1) If the records in error are simply to be rerun through this process, then have the RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD reset to 4 and restart the job in the Process Controller, or (2) if the fix is to discard the data related to the error, then reset the RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD to 201, which represents a permanent data error (TVNDR_REBT_CD.TYP_CD = 176).
If the RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD value of 101 is left in the RECN_SUMM_STAT_CD table then the corresponding truncate script will not be allowed to truncate the table and clean up old data.
